{# The boiler in the utility recess. `state` (fioul | fioul-broken | pellet)
   picks BOTH the asset and the local variant class: fioul and fioul-broken
   share one asset whose layers the class toggles (flame vs smoke/alarm/sign),
   while pellet is a silhouette of its own (body + silo) — a different fuel
   shouldn't look like the same machine repainted. #}
{% props state = 'fioul' %}
<g class="boiler boiler--{{ state }}"{{ attributes }}>{{ include(state == 'pellet' ? 'game/scene/assets/boiler-pellet.svg' : 'game/scene/assets/boiler-fioul.svg') }}</g>
